# Codebase2Prompt

A simple tool to generate prompts from codebase structure and content.

## Installation

```bash
pip install Codebase2Prompt
```

## Usage

```bash
Codebase2Prompt [OPTIONS]
```

### Options

- `--exclude`: Directories or files to exclude (can be used multiple times)
- `--lines`: Number of lines to show from each definition (default: 10)

### Example

```bash
Codebase2Prompt --exclude tests --lines 5
```

## Features

- Recursively scans codebase
- Shows hierarchical structure
- Includes class/function definitions
- Customizable output with --lines parameter
- Exclude specific directories/files with --exclude

## Development

Install dependencies:

```bash
poetry install
```

Run tests:

```bash
poetry run pytest
```

